Class TextEngine

java.lang.Object
TextEngine
public abstract class TextEngine extends Object
ASCIIADVENTURER Caden Finley Albert Tucker Grijesh Shrestha The TextEngine class provides methods for printing text with delays, clearing the console screen, and waiting for user input. It also includes methods for checking the validity of input commands, parsing commands, and matching commands against a list of possible commands.
Version:
1.0
Author:
ASCIIADVENTURERS

  • Method Details

    • setWidth

      public static void setWidth()
      Sets the terminal width by querying the terminal for its current width. On Windows, it uses the "mode con" command, and on Unix-like systems, it uses the "tput cols" command. If the terminal width cannot be determined, a default width of 80 is used.

    • printWithDelays

      public static void printWithDelays(String data, boolean buffer) throws InterruptedException
      Throws:
      InterruptedException

    • printNoDelay

      public static void printNoDelay(String data, boolean buffer)
      Prints the given data with delays between characters based on the speed setting. If buffering is enabled, it adds a prompt to press enter to type after the text is printed.
      Parameters:
      data - The data to be printed.
      buffer - If true, adds a prompt to press enter to type after the text is printed.

    • clearScreen

      public static void clearScreen()
      Clears the console screen. This method determines the operating system and clears the screen accordingly. For Windows, it uses a combination of ANSI escape codes and the "clear" command. For other operating systems, it uses only ANSI escape codes.

    • enterToNext

      public static void enterToNext()
      Adds a pause and waits for the user to press Enter to continue. If the application is not in testing mode, it will print a message prompting the user to press Enter and then wait for the Enter key to be pressed.

    • checkValidInput

      public static Boolean checkValidInput(String command)
      Checks if the input command is valid.
      Parameters:
      command - the input command to be checked
      Returns:
      true if the command is not null, not empty, and not an empty string; false otherwise

    • parseCommand

      public static String parseCommand(String command, String[] possibleCommands)
      Parses the input command and matches it against a list of possible commands. If the command is found in the list of illegal commands, it returns the command as is. Otherwise, it tries to find the best match from the possible commands.
      Parameters:
      command - the input command to be parsed
      possibleCommands - an array of possible commands to match against
      Returns:
      the matched command if found, otherwise the original command
